Ranger Help for: advancement
============================

SUMMARY:
Rangers advance through guild levels 1 to 15. Each guild level grants
slots that you spend to learn new skills. Higher guild levels give
more slots per level (4 at level 1, up to 20 at level 15).

BEFORE YOU CAN ADVANCE:
You must set all three of these first (one-time choices):
  setprime <terrain>    Your primary terrain
  setsecond <terrain>   Your secondary terrain
  setenemy <race>       Your enemy species

HOW TO ADVANCE:
Ranger guild levels are earned automatically with Ranger XP from battle.
The lodge and your quiver report your progress:

  rcost                 See Ranger XP and slot progress
  radvance level        Advance your game level (costs experience)
  radvance guild        See Ranger XP and any blocked advancement
  radvance <stat>       Raise str, dex, con, int, wis, or chr

These commands require you to be in the wilderness (not a city,
indoors, or at a dock). You can also use 'advance' and 'cost'
when visiting the lodge.

Your guild level cannot exceed your game level. So to reach guild
level 5, you need to be at least game level 5.

LEARNING SKILLS:
Once you have slots, spend them on skills:
  skilltree             See the full skill tree
  learn                 See what skills you can learn right now
  learn <skill>         Learn a skill (costs slots)
  learn cost <skill>    Check the cost before committing

Skills have prerequisites - learning one skill unlocks others. Start
with 'forage' (your first available skill) and branch out from there.
Use 'skilltree' to plan your path.

COST FACTORS:
- Skill slots are the only cost for learning Ranger skills.
- Skills cost more SP to use outside your primary/secondary terrain.
- Alignment far from neutral increases SP costs for all skills.

